                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/8190b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Ministers in Sweden, Norway, Denmark, the Netherlands,
                            and Greece</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-25T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confer with Allied colleagues before recommending changes in enemy trading list,
                    and if agreement results from conference, report in duplicate simultaneously to
                    Department and Ensign Frothingham, United States Embassy, London, decisions and
                    reasons. If disagreement results, send your opinion and variant opinions of
                    colleagues with reasons. In each case give nationality and residence of person
                    or association recommended for addition or removal from list. Repeat to
                    consuls.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
